{"albumName":"Hold Your Colour","artistName":"Pendulum","info":"Hold Your Colour is the debut studio album by the Australian drum and bass band Pendulum, released on 25 July 2005 and later reissued in 2007 by Breakbeat Kaos. The album was mastered by Stuart Hawkes at Metropolis in London.[1] The album features collaborations with artists such as the DJs Fresh and TC, the MCs $pyda and Fats, vocalists from bands Freestylers and Halogen, and guitarists from bands Karnivool and Concord Dawn, together with Peredur ap Gwynedd.\r\n\r\nThe original release consisted of 14 tracks, with a later re-release that replaced 2 tracks in the album with 2 new ones.\r\n\r\n(Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hold_Your_Colour)","filePath":"/uploads/c66bbdecf64d9d11491e49ee826088d1","_id":"L1m3gG7OFRPGGJ7c"}
{"albumName":"Mass Media Constant","artistName":"Zircon","info":"zircon (Andrew Aversa) has been creating sonic worlds with synthesizers and organic instruments since 2003. His signature style incorporates elements from genres like drum and bass, progressive breakbeat, trance, dubstep, and future bass, with deep melodic and atmospheric writing that can be enjoyed on the dancefloor and far beyond. (Source: Spotify bio)\r\n\r\nThe album \"Mass Media Constant\", released in 2009, consists of 10 tracks. \r\n\r\nListen on: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=OLAK5uy_l8LrOFsGDSoOvULEm-FmGKSxZonl-BuQc&si=E1ANrK2i6NnvmxZx","filePath":"/uploads/84cc786267838b2ee82b944946c9b06a","_id":"Q7kLfKluf4sZen78"}
{"albumName":"They Left Me with the Sword","artistName":"Paris Texas","info":"They Left Me with the Sword is an EP released by the Los Angeles Duo Paris Texas. During the midst of the Chromakopia Tour, Paris Texas would surprise-release two pairs of EP's, one titled \"They Left Me with the Sword\" & the other titled \"They Left Me With A Gun\" only a week from each other. The first was released on the 21st of February, and the other was released on the 28th of February 2025. It's their first album that delves into developing their own sound and really honing that into something enjoyable and relaxing to listen to.\r\n(Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paris_Texas_(hip-hop_group)","filePath":"/uploads/5ae6a9b48d8bc335887292b3b5b97283","_id":"XIqKXbsg8lcY455w"}
{"albumName":"Fête de la Vanille","artistName":"Lucy Bedroque","info":"Fête de la Vanille (which translates to Vanilla Festival) is his second official EP that was released on streaming services Oct. 3rd of 2024. With it only containing 6 tracks and it being 19 minutes in length. It takes inspiration from the Japanese music genre Shibuya-Kei. Though his music career began with creating lo-fi beats, he became involved with many online communities around the “digicore” scene during the COVID-19 lockdown. This inspired him to experiment with using his own voice under the alias loru. (Source: https://genius.com/albums/Lucy-bedroque/Fete-de-la-vanille) \r\n","filePath":"/uploads/34cec70ceca75231350857658be7e186","_id":"bIHsMk7t5dWbwMQX"}
{"albumName":"Revengeseekerz","artistName":"Jane Remover","info":"Revengeseekerz serves as Jane's 3rd Studio Album, which was released on April 4th of 2025. Revengeseekerz’s sound contains elements of rage and EDM, but the production style is uniquely Jane’s, with several samples referencing video games such as Pokémon, Mario, and Fortnite. (Source: https://genius.com/albums/Jane-remover/Revengeseekerz)","filePath":"/uploads/b7aebb6b06daf607fd051f0a20a00847","_id":"dLLXNUSAtMboOZkk"}
{"albumName":"Adventures Beyond The Ultraworld","artistName":"The Orb","info":"The Orb's Adventures Beyond the Ultraworld is the debut studio album by the English electronic music group the Orb, released as a double album on 2 April 1991 by Big Life. It is a segued, progressive record evoking a psychedelic trip which draws from various genres (including ambient, house, dub reggae, and hip hop) and incorporates a huge number of samples and sound effects. Much of the album was recorded after founding member Jimmy Cauty left the group, leaving Alex Paterson as the central member, with additional contributions by Kris Weston, Andy Falconer and several others.\r\n(Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Orb%27s_Adventures_Beyond_the_Ultraworld)\r\n\r\nFeatures 10 tracks, listen here: https://youtube.com/playlist?list=OLAK5uy_mkoc8wXczkwynhGUwl3PT9wdqzD2EOBGY&si=Wvn0yI4jSpKi01Tf","filePath":"/uploads/3b24f5ec6e6c064232938e7f77428db5","_id":"eC5s9xgoMsdDVuuV"}
